</ul>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id="Controversy">Controversy</h2><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Monument_to_the_Belgian_Pioneers_in_Congo&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5" title="Edit section: Controversy"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Since the 1980s, the monument has become increasingly controversial. On the one hand, the glorification of Belgium's colonial past has been increasingly contested. On the other hand, the words <i>Arab slave trader</i> on one of the inscriptions has been a source of contention for the Arab Muslim population in Brussels, partly due to the proximity of the <a href="/wiki/Great_Mosque_of_Brussels" title="Great Mosque of Brussels">Great Mosque of Brussels</a>. After a complaint by the <a href="/wiki/Arab_League" title="Arab League">Arab League</a>, the words <i>Araabschen / arabe</i> were removed in 1988.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-:0&#95;1-8" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-:0-1"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>1<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> The words were restored in 1992 after a demand by the <a href="/wiki/Belgian_nationalism" title="Belgian nationalism">Belgian nationalist</a> <i>Cercle royal des anciens officiers des campagnes d'Afrique</i>, but the French version was again removed in 2005.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-Apache&#95;2-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Apache-2"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>2<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> In 2011, <a href="/wiki/Ecolo" title="Ecolo">Ecolo</a> politician Évelyne Huytebroeck decided to include an educational caption.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-6" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-6"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>6<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> In 2020, two <a href="/wiki/Far-right_politics" title="Far-right politics">far-right</a> politicians from <a href="/wiki/Vlaams_Belang" title="Vlaams Belang">Vlaams Belang</a>, <a href="/wiki/Dries_Van_Langenhove" title="Dries Van Langenhove">Dries Van Langenhove</a> and <a href="/wiki/Bob_De_Brabandere" title="Bob De Brabandere">Bob De Brabandere</a>, once more restored the words <i>Araabschen / arabe</i>, as a reaction on what they described as a "current-day <i><a href="/wiki/Beeldenstorm" title="Beeldenstorm">Beeldenstorm</a></i> and hypocritical cult of apologies".<sup id="cite&#95;ref-HLN&#95;2-7-20&#95;3-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-HLN_2-7-20-3"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>3<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> The words were again removed shortly thereafter.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-HLN&#95;8-7-20&#95;4-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-HLN_8-7-20-4"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>4<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> 
</p>
<ul class="gallery mw-gallery-packed">
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 134.66666666667px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 132.66666666667px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Monument_voor_de_Belgische_pioniers_Jubelpark_detail.jpg" class="mw-file-description" title="The Belgian soldier and the Arab slave trader, with a part of the inscription removed"><img alt="The Belgian soldier and the Arab slave trader, with a part of the inscription removed" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ab/Monument_voor_de_Belgische_pioniers_Jubelpark_detail.jpg/250px-Monument_voor_de_Belgische_pioniers_Jubelpark_detail.jpg" decoding="async" width="133" height="200" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ab/Monument_voor_de_Belgische_pioniers_Jubelpark_detail.jpg/500px-Monument_voor_de_Belgische_pioniers_Jubelpark_detail.jpg 2x" data-file-width="3264" data-file-height="4912" /></a></span></div>
			<div class="gallerytext">The Belgian soldier and the Arab slave trader, with a part of the inscription removed</div>
		</li>
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 152px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Detail_of_the_Monument_to_the_Belgian_Pioneers_in_Congo.jpg" class="mw-file-description" title="Modified inscription Belgian military heroism crushes the (Arab) slave trader, April 2022"><img alt="Modified inscription Belgian military heroism crushes the (Arab) slave trader, April 2022" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cb/Detail_of_the_Monument_to_the_Belgian_Pioneers_in_Congo.jpg/250px-Detail_of_the_Monument_to_the_Belgian_Pioneers_in_Congo.jpg" decoding="async" width="150" height="200" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cb/Detail_of_the_Monument_to_the_Belgian_Pioneers_in_Congo.jpg/500px-Detail_of_the_Monument_to_the_Belgian_Pioneers_in_Congo.jpg 2x" data-file-width="3024" data-file-height="4032" /></a></span></div>
			<div class="gallerytext">Modified inscription <i>Belgian military heroism crushes the (Arab) slave trader</i>, April 2022</div>
		</li>
